    slug: "a-guide-to-salat-prayer",
    description: `A Guide to Salat (Prayer) is a comprehensive English-language instructional book that provides detailed, step-by-step guidance on how to perform the Islamic prayer (salah) correctly. The book serves as a practical manual for both new Muslims who are learning to pray for the first time and for practicing Muslims who want to ensure that their prayers are performed in accordance with the authentic Sunnah of Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him). The guide covers every aspect of the prayer, from the pre-prayer requirements to the specific supplications recited in each position, making it one of the most thorough and user-friendly prayer manuals available in the English language.

The book begins with the essential prerequisites for prayer, including the conditions that must be met before prayer can be valid — such as being in a state of ritual purity (wudu or ghusl), facing the qiblah, covering the awrah (body parts that must be covered during prayer), and praying at the correct times. Detailed illustrated instructions are provided for performing wudu (ablution), with each step clearly depicted and explained, along with the supplications to be recited during and after wudu. The book then proceeds to a complete walkthrough of the prayer itself, covering every movement and recitation from the opening takbeer to the final salam. Each position — standing (qiyam), bowing (ruku), prostration (sujud), and sitting between the two prostrations (jalsah) — is described with the appropriate supplications provided in Arabic text, English transliteration, and English translation, ensuring that readers can follow along regardless of their level of Arabic proficiency.

Beyond the basic obligatory prayer, the book covers a range of additional topics that are essential for a complete understanding of salah. These include the different categories of prayer (fard, wajib, sunnah, and nafl), the specific rulings for congregational prayer and the Friday prayer (Jumuah), the prayer of the traveler (qasr), the prayer during illness or while sitting, the funeral prayer (janazah), and the Eid prayers. The book also addresses common mistakes and errors that people make during prayer, providing corrections based on the authentic hadith. Diagrams and illustrations throughout the book show the correct postures and hand positions, helping readers visualize each movement. The guide is widely used in new Muslim classes, Islamic schools, and daawah programs, and is frequently recommended by imams and teachers as an essential reference for anyone who wants to establish or improve their daily prayer practice.`,
